<paragraph blockId="14.[859,1369,1316,1338]" box="[859,1369,1316,1338]" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
<heading box="[859,1369,1316,1338]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(OSTEN SACKEN, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Osten Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[859,1369,1316,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satur">
<emphasis box="[859,1091,1316,1337]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">COPESTYLUM SATUR</emphasis>
(OSTEN SACKEN, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[806,1422,1354,1744]" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
<emphasis box="[806,1158,1354,1376]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
Larva and puparium (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1144,1354,1376]" captionStart="Figures 20–22" captionStartId="41.[164,254,829,848]" captionTargetBox="[421,1184,197,797]" captionTargetId="figure-0@41.[419,1187,195,799]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figures 20–22. Third stage larval Copestylum, whole larva, head to the right; scale bar = 6 mm. 20, Copestylum satur; 21, Copestylum tetetzoi sp. nov.; 22, Copestylum vittatum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443492/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Dorsal abdominal vestiture confined to medial areas on the transverse bands. Ventral abdominal vestiture of varying length with anterior ends of folds with longer setae than posterior ends. Posterior breathing tube yellowbrown, surface corrugated and shiny, about half width of puparium. TR barely discernable. AP bulging at apex, tapering slightly and 0.75¥ as long as a pupal spiracle. Spiracular openings at apex with simple s-shaped curves. Pupal spiracles long, about 3¥ as long as basal width, slightly outcurved, shiny red with openings in upper third and separated by 1.4¥ their length (
<figureCitation box="[963,1045,1721,1744]" captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="47.[164,254,1555,1574]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1523]" captionTargetId="figure-0@47.[323,1283,195,1525]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="Figures 48–53. Pupal spiracles of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs. 48, 50, Copestylum fornax; 48, dorsolateral view length 0.38 mm; 50, whole view from above scale as indicated; 49, Copestylum satur, lateral view length 0.73 mm; 51, 53, Copestylum marginatum; 51, dorsolateral view length 0.82 mm; 53, sculpture between openings, view from above; 52, Copestylum limbipenne, sculpture between openings, view from above." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443508/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="712" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[806,1421,1789,1903]" lastBlockId="15.[164,779,198,342]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="712" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
<emphasis box="[806,1209,1789,1811]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Osten Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1009,1209,1789,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satur">Copestylum satur</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Townsend, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[806,1125,1819,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fornax">
<emphasis box="[806,914,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. fornax</emphasis>
(Townsend, 1895)
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Williston, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraudulentum">
<emphasis box="[1229,1421,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. fraudulentum</emphasis>
(Williston, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="711" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraudulentum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="711">C. fraudulentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shallow TR and vestiture confined to medial areas of abdominal transverse folds and from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[164,271,228,250]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fornax">
<emphasis box="[164,271,228,250]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">C. fornax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the yellow-brown, slightly tapering posterior breathing tube and the longer pupal spiracles which are about 3¥ basal length and which are separated by less than 2¥ their length.
</paragraph>
